hopobject.body: An accountancy practice intivar shipping My background isn't in climate science, but it is very intensive in science, math and statistics. My educational and professional background includes the hard, social, health and biological sciences, extensive applied mathematics and statistics, optics, radiation, absorption, lighting, wave physics and most importantly, multi-variable linear regression modeling. The early climate models were nothing but edited financial models, and the principles and statistics that guide the multi-variable models used to define the stock market don't change just because they are being used to model the climate. Math is the language of science, and if you understand math, what branch of science it is applied to really doesn't matter.
